style.text:
From the _Overview _table on the **Overview** sheet it is evident that there have been a number of access denials in the past seven days and many more in the past 28 days. Has this affected a number of different users, or are there specific users who are being denied access frequently?




To investigate this issue, review the _Users Denied Access_ table on either the **User Detail** sheet or the **Login Access History** sheet. The table lists users who were denied access, when they were last denied, and how many times each user was denied access.

customErrorMessage.calcCond: No access denials are associated with your current selections.

style.text:
Check the _Login Access Passes per User_ table on the **Login ****Access History** sheet to see if any users are exceeding the 28\-day access threshold \(10\). Those users would be candidates for a dedicated user login pass.

In this case, however, no login pass users have exceeded the threshold in last 28 days.

Because there are no login pass users who should be given user pass access, resolving the problem of login access denials can probably be handled by allocating more tokens to the specific groups whose users are being denied access. License tokens are allocated in the Qlik Management Console.

customErrorMessage.calcCond: No license usage is associated with your current selections.
